x4freetext: , Cs-30 Cyclotron at Miami Beach
Isotopically enriched 66Zn(99%), 67Zn(91.5%) and
68Zn(98%) targets.
Targets were prepared on Ni foils by electrolytic
deposition. Thickness were measured by weight.
Stacks containing several enriched-Zn target foils and
Ti and Cu monitor foils and Al foils as energy degrader
were irradiated with 26 MeV, 200-600nA proton beams.
The beam energy was determined by using monitor foils
with +-0.3 MeV accuracy. Energy degradation was
calculated using table of Williamson et al. Rapport
Cea-R-3042, Saclay, France.
Cross sections were corrected for 100% enrichment.
Energy uncertainty of the incident proton beam
after 10MeV energy degradation was estimated to be
about 0.6 MeV.
The estimated uncertainties on cross
sections were calculated by summing up quadratically
the possible individual relative errors:
Counting statistics       1-5%
Detector efficiency       5%
Decay data                2%
Number of arget nuclei   7%                  D
Beam current              5%
Data were taken from Table 1 of the original paper
